A search is under way for a man who absconded from a south-east London mental health facility on Sunday.Abderrahmane Ariba, 30, was last seen at about 09:30 BST while he was on an escorted walk.Mr Ariba may have travelled from the facility in Beckenham to Marble Arch then Croydon where he was last seen.The Metropolitan Police has advised people not to approach him but to call 999 instead.
